<text>I have low expectations when you‚Äôre eating in the middle of nowhere, or in most National Parks. A restaurant that is a ‚Äú3-star‚Äù in a city is ‚Äú5-star‚Äù for a National Park but this place truly deserves all five stars. The decor emulates an old western saloon while feeling clean and modern (it is only ~2 years old). The food is really good, the prime rib and ribs weren‚Äôt the best I‚Äôve had of course, but they‚Äôre items I would consider eating in a city and I wholeheartedly look forward to eating here again next time we visit.< /text>< userid>

<rating>1</rating>< review>
Almost no kind words for this place! Two heaping plates of destroyed ingredients were on the table when we left. It can‚Äôt be that hard to produce two omelettes with hash browns and toast that are worth eating. It was like they dumped the spinach right out of the can onto the eggs. Between the water and grease from the omelette the deep fried seasoned potatoes being  passed off for hash browns were doing the backstroke while sopping up the mess. There was nothing to taste beyond the low rent spinach. The other omelette was no better with a giant glob of Swiss cheese protecting everything under it. Even with the onions it was tasteless. Thee only redeeming aspect of this experience was the nice lady who took the order and listened politely to my complaint, albeit with no suggested remedy. All this for just $19 per plate!< /review>

Super fun saloon with solid food and service. The food ain't anything to write home about, but it's as good as you can expect while camping out in the middle of Death Valley. The highlight of the restaurant would definitely be the decor. They've done a magnificent job recreating a saloon from the Old Wild Wild West, complete with mounted animal heads and wooden furniture.

I ordered the baby back ribs, and they were pretty good - just a little on the tough side. The brussel sprouts and pancetta was reasonably tasty, though way over-oiled.< /text>

<Name>Kyle Reighard</Name><pictures>None</pictures>< Review>
Can‚Äôt say enough good about this place. Totally unique, inviting establishment open to non resort guests as well. Casey at the front door was very helpful with getting me seated faster than the anticipated wait on a Saturday night. She was also very informative on the local area. John, the GM told me the history of the bar and talked with me outside for about 10 minutes to explain the local areas to see dark sky views of Death Valley as I was just passing through for the night. The food was outstanding, fresh and reasonably priced in a restored western saloon. For my first time in the state of California I couldn‚Äôt have found a more welcoming and friendly place to eat a meal. Thanks again.</Review>

<Date>1603171280098<//Date><Name>Liz Mead Lantz< /Name><rating>2< /rating>< Review>
We stayed at the Ranch for the weekend. This is one of three restaurants in this part of the park so not a lot of options and they know it so everything is super expensive. Since it‚Äôs the only restaurant we would go there for breakfast lunch and dinner. It‚Äôs the only place in the hotel to get coffee because the hotel‚Äôs coffee shop inexplicably opens at 1pm and they removed all of the self serve coffee stations due to covid. Instead of having a to go coffee station, everyone has to sit at a table, order a coffee to go, wait for the bill, and finally 10 minutes later you can be on your way. Lunch was ok but they don‚Äôt allow you to put your name in for a table. Instead they put you in a seating area and try to memorize which order you will be seated. They forgot we were waiting and finally asked 45 minutes later what we were doing in the waiting area and we explained we were waiting for a table. For dinner you‚Äôre looking at a $150-200 meal since there aren‚Äôt cheap options it‚Äôs just $50 steaks and $11 sides. Even the chicken is $50! Well it didn‚Äôt matter because they said we needed a reservation. We ate at the patio at the inn instead which was much better and less expensive. If you are staying at this hotel just pack some of your own food if possible and you will have much more time to explore the park and save some $$.</Review>

My dad and I went here on a recent trip, and given the current situation with the pandemic, the restaurant was empty. I wasn't super hungry, so my only meal was the bread bowl of chili. < review>
The Jug Jug is a place to drink in Granada Hills north of Rinaldi. Theres another place in the same shopping center to drink but dont go there unless looking for trouble. The place is owned by this badass named Duke. The bartenders are all strippers the Duke meets during the daytime. Because of this the bartenders are super friendly. My friend goes here every night thinking they all want to bang. I keep telling him the only thing that interests them in his pants is his wallet, but the joke goes over his head. Be careful when they ask if you want a big beer, as the big beer is basicly a 40 with the top cut off and a handle attched to the side. Duke will encourage you to drink it fast then laugh at your feeble attempt. He will then slug the beer in 3 seconds and insult your manhood. You will unsuccessfully try to replicate his method and barf on the Barper (bartender/stripper). Then go home and throw up some more. I recommend the Blogie as its just as good going down as it is coming up.<//review>

<rate>5< /rate><Text>What started from a tradition has become a frequent thing. Jug Jug is still the best sports bar in the san fernando valley. Unlike most bars I have been to, there is no judgement. You come any day and any night, and you just enjoy some good brew and if you are hungry.. some really good korean food. Now, the one snack that is lacking is their tortilla chips and salsa. They were once famous for their salsa, until they stopped giving it out to customers. Why? I don't know. But still worth the trip to come here and mingle with friends. It does get loud during game night and when it's a busy night. The music is loud, but bearable. Wish they do karaoke still... I miss their one time karaoke night they had. I took my friends here and they enjoyed jug jug the most which was the karaoke night they had. The owner of this establishment is very friendly and is always out and about. He's great with the customers! I come here for the Soju Cocktails and the beer. Now the specialty that I also come here for are the fries and the spicy wings. Did I say that right.. oh yes I Did. They have the best sweet and very spicy chicken wings. Wherever I may be with friend eating somewhere else, we always need to get our order of spicy chicken wings at Jug Jug. Usually we will make the trip if we are close by. Thats how great these wings are. Definitely a great place to eat, drink, and enjoy company!!</Text><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< response>

< UserId.>
104699402925738896219< /UserId.>
< name>
Daniel Yang<//name>
<time>1518343364680</time>< rate>
5</rate>
<text>I used to eat here regularly 5-10 years ago.  I stopped going because it always got so crowded, it just wasn't worth the wait.  Fast forward to 2017/2018.  I've been eating nothing but KHD Baekjong, Quarters, Parks, Soot Bull Jeep in Ktown in 2017.  I was doing weekly ventures to Ookook and Gen, and Red Castle bbq for all you can eat in 2015-2016.  I revisit this place 2 weeks ago, and I forgot how much I loved it.  The ban chan (side dishes) leave nothing to be desired. It's literally every side you need and want.  The thin cut brisket and pork belly are excellent.  The galbi (marinated short rib) is also good and all u can eat on our $21.99 per person option.  (There is a $19.99 dinner option that doesn't include the galbi and some other better cuts of meat).  The steamed egg and kimchi/soybean soup is also all u can eat, the limited sushi roll menu is all you can eat (I would stay away from these fillers, as they are packed with rice and not much of a step up from supermarket/buffet rolls) and they leave 2 carafes of water so you never have to ask for a refill.  After all is said and done, at this price point, it is truly my favorite.  Are there better places?  Of course.  Are there more expensive/cheaper places?  Of course. But everything here is everything I grew up on, and is what I expect Korean BBQ to be all about. Nothing more, nothing less.  And the price is fantastic.</text>< Pics>

<UserId.>107807796738156989480<//UserId.><Name>Ajani Billington< /Name>< Date>
1531698388398< /Date>
< rate>
1<//rate>
< Review>
This food tastes like someone heard about BBQ and soul food, tried to make it, but didn't bother to make it taste good. I've had approximations of soul food before but never this lazily concocted. It's as if the chef had no intention of ever eating this food, so they didn't care H how it tasted. The greens were bitter and lacking much flavor. The cornbread was dry and crumbly. The BBQ sauce simply isn't good (barely any spices and too much vinegar and a watery consistency). I gave the ribs to my dog. The meat on the ribs tasted old and was going bad. The fat on the ribs was not rendered, and was therefore inedible. The yams tasted like they're only seasoned in burnt white sugar (no butter or cinnamon) and they were just sitting in water. Frankly, I'm scared to try to banana pudding.</Review>

<review>Excellent first impression and continued quality. If they need to substitute something they will call almost right away after sending in your order.
Some of the items I've ordered for delivery (a few times) were:
Ribs (large ribs - I'm the kind of person that likes some fat on meat and was not disappointed).
Pull Pork (Comes cooked with sauce already added; good, but not as good a choice as the ribs or Brisket / tri-tip).
Links - Beef (Tasted as expected - good choice for one of the meat options).
Brisket (sometimes unavailable earlier in the morning; Large portion - very good).
Side of Mac & Cheese (one of the best in the area after having sampled several others - excellent choice if you're looking for macaroni and cheese from a barbecue place).
Tri-tip (came as a substitute for Brisket): another good choice.
Side of Yams (between average and good - first choice would be Mac and Cheese but this isn't a bad choice either).

Only less-than-stellar item: Closed on Mondays at least at the time of this review.<//review><gmap_id>0x809ad7098388c9e1:0xfb4dc203ba96a5a4<//gmap_id>< user_name>

< review>
Halo HID Xenon Headlamps for my 05 Ram 1500 were not the plug and play replacement units ProTuning Labs suggested they were.   As a precaution, went ahead and bought all the "recommended " accessories.

Package arrived very slowly, even had to email their customer service to determine if package had been shipped as it was already a day late from their own maximum projected delivery window.

As you can see from the attached picture,  the units are sharp looking.  However, they did not come with ANY installation instructions.  So,  not wanting to bugger up these high dollar units,  I spent almost the same amount again to have them professionally installed (2.5 hours labor)

So here's the fun part, hardly a week or so later I go to turn on my lights,  hear a loud pop from my stereo, and now I'm down one light...i email their customer service and get a checklist of trouble shooting procedures which involved removing and swapping various components between sides to narrow down the problem.  I explain i had them professionally installed and wouldn't know what I was looking for,  so did they have a wiring diagram they could send? No... could y'all help with the labor cost of having them checked at the installer...Hell no

Ok,  when I get some extra cash I'll have them checked out and hope I don't get a ticket meanwhile (I didn't). Finally determined the ballast had gone bad,  again e-mailed customer service which informed me the units are under a 1 year warranty so the ballast is free, well almost,  I was on the hook for the $9 S&H fee.  So they told me go to this link,  buy the part and they'll reimburse me everything else.

Ok,  so $13 dollars later, I was tempted not to go thru the hassle of dealing with Customer Support again... but I did.

The ballast took almost a week to arrived,  and I had an appointment set to spend another $50 at the installer the following Tuesday. When that very night... blammo, out goes the other light.

So to sum up,  for a $270 set of headlamps,  I've had to lay out $250 for the initial install,  $10 for the trouble shooting that one side, $9 S&H for the free replacement,  $50 for the r&r on one side,  which in all likelihood will have to be repeated in the other side so $378 dollars operating costs for about 15 hours of night driving.

Sound fun? Then by all means do business with these folks<//review>

< Text>
FITS VEHICLES WITH BARN DOORS!
Let me start by stating that I have ordered LED tail lights from 2 other companies that did NOT fit my Suburban with cargo (barn) doors. The issue is the narrow clearance in the bottom of the lights due to the door hinge (for barn doors). The other LED tail lights that I ordered were designed with a back up light at the bottom which did not allow for enough clearance to fit a vehicle WITH barn doors.
YOUR item, 03-CD2000LED DOES fit a Suburban/Tahoe/Yukon with barn doors! They are designed with the back up light in the CENTER of the light, keeping the tail light narrow at the very bottom. And since the 2 electrical boxes inside each tail light are not pre-attached to the light, I removed the plastic peel to expose the adhesive and attached them a little higher in the tail light to avoid contact with the door hinge.
I received the LED tail lights yesterday and installed them. They look very nice. I  recommend this product, it will fit all Suburban/Tahoe/Yukon vehicles with tailgate type door or barn doors.

Keith C.< /Text>

<Review>First my headlights were back ordered, then I had to choose another headlight.   Arrived, looked good, but install of HID headlights is a pain. Was too busy at work and had a spare vehicle so I parked it...started driving it again 3 months later and the LED halo starts to flicker then stops working.

I take it to a repair shop and the resistors for the HID are not working properly which is why the one headlight was not working consistently.  The LED‚Äôs seem to have burned out and the only way to replace them is to send the headlight back or buy a new one.

So repair shop adds $160 to the tab and takes out the resistors and HID‚Äôs and replaces the bulbs with LED‚Äôs and just disconnects the Halo‚Äôs since only one side works.

<text>Johnnie Mallott
¬∑ 4 seconds ago
I recently ordered a new tail light for my wife's 2015 GMC Yukon Denali. I was in a hurry when I ordered it and ended up with the wrong part. It was completely my fault. Had I taken the time and called first, I could have saved myself more time in the end. I was in communication with the support team via email to coordinate the return. I was worried I would be charged the 20% restocking fee, but I tried REALLY hard to get the tail light set cleaned and put back in the original shipping arrangement and original packaging. Once I did that, I used the shipping return label to drop off the package at FedEx ( I was there MAYBE 4 min) then walked away. I used FedEx tracking to keep an eye out for when it was delivered to ProTuningLabs. Once it was, I gave them a couple days to process it, then emailed the support team about my refund. They informed me that although their policy states they charge a 20% restocking, they were refunding my entire purchase amount. This just goes to show you that a little effort on both ends, goes a LONG way toward making both parties happy. I would definitely recommend ProTuningLabs for online parts ordering. Just make sure you take the time to know what your ordering and if you aren't sure, just call them. They have proven to be very helpful despite some of the negative reviews I see on this forum. Thanks PTL! I'll recommend you in the future for sure!<//text>< pictures>

<review>Amazing, fast service and great looking products.
I ordered LED projector headlights for my 2015 Camaro and they were delivered before I had even received a tracking number for them. The confirmation email said 'expect 3-5 business days' or something like that, but my order was at my front door the next day. The headlights didn't come with any installation instructions, which I emailed the support team about. However, by the time they got back to me later that day, I had already finished the installation because it was so easy. Literally all I had to do was look at the headlight housing to figure out what to do. If you can tell the difference between red and black wires, you can instal these headlights with no instructions whatsoever. As far as the headlights themselves, they are noticeably better than factory halogen bulbs, but aren't so stupid bright that you'll blind oncoming traffic. Perfectly in between. < Review>
These are falsely marketed as "plug and play." I ordered aftermarket LED projector headlights specific to my Jetta mk6 ('11-'14).  This product does not match depiction, nor description in linked video content.. The secondary electrical fitment does not match OEM electrical terminals. This would require electrical re-wiring. The received product does not have the same wiring as the advertised product.

The only information guide included with the product is written in incoherent broken English.

Contacted ProTuning via email 3/26. l Will update review when fixed.

*Update:
- The load resistors fell off the assembly. They get extremely hot, and the manufacturer didn‚Äôt use a proper high temperature adhesive or a proper mount location. Furthermore, the manufacturer thought it would be wise to install a device that reaches 260 degrees Fahrenheit on a thermoplastic.
-Load resistors were not even the correct resistance to simulate the OEM voltage and prevent the computer from throwing a bulb-out code.
-This clear plastic part of the light assembly chipped from wear in the natural elements, after just under a year.
-The assemblies wasn‚Äôt properly sealed by the manufacturer from moisture.
-The electrical elements ultimately failed.
-The OEM assemblies were reinstalled and the problems disappeared.
-No warranty.

Conclusion: Complete waste of money. Extremely cheap, inferior, poorly-manufactured product. ProTuning will not refund/exchange, unless product has not been installed.</Review>

< Text>
Wish there was a 1/4 star .... Save your money and headaches ... DO NOT BUY ANYTHING FROM THIS COMPANY.  There customer service excuses is just like water running down a facet - keep going without stopping.  There are the most dishonest, false product advertisement merchant I have ever dealt with.  First, they sold me a product which arrived damaged and late.  The item was purchased to be shipped overseas into a shipping container.  During numerous conversation with a person name  "Raphael M", I told him that I would glue the broken part on and after installation, I would see how it holds together and report back.  He said "OK" but upon reporting back, it was nothing but B.S so I could keep the product past the date where I could NOT file a claim with my credit card company for reimbursement.  NOTE: The damaged product did not fully met OEM specifications as ProTuning Lab claim.  I will post the entire conversations with ProTuning Lab Inc.

--------------------------
Mar 22 to ProTuningLab Inc support

Hello Customer Care,

My order was delivered today while I was at work.  Upon returning home and verifying the contents in the boxes, I noticed one of the white boxes was packed differently.  The box in question had the "left" headlight housing assembly.  It had compressed foam packaging which leads me to believe this item was previously sold/open/etc.  There was also a "grey piece of plastic with a hole" inside the box.

--------------------------
MAR 27, 2017  |  11:14AM PDT
Original message
Customer wrote:

Raphael,

I am traveling next month so at that time, I will install the lights and
see how they hold up then upon my return, I will follow-up with your
regarding compensation offer.

Note:
Was it a "new" light because it did not come packaged like the other one?

--------------------------
MAR 27, 2017  |  03:52PM PDT
Raphael M replied:

Please let us know the outcome of your troubleshoot, let us know what you want to do with the order. Your order has been notated about you being on vacation. Thank you.
Thank you,

--------------------------

May 4 (6 days ago)

to support, support
Raphael,

I have returned from travel.

The same headlight with the damaged bracket had more issues.

The socket for the "turn signal/DRL" was not OEM sized-correct.  It would not work with the OEM bulb/connector.  The socket had to be modified in order for the bulb/connector to fit securely.

It appears that the item was sold previously and returned when it was found not to be compatible to OEM specifications.

The other headlight fit perfectly which was a sealed item upon receipt.

As I had initially mentioned, the lights were shipped to another country.

Where do we go from here regarding the light issue?

--------------------------

MAY 06, 2017  |  05:48PM PDT
Raphael M replied:

The only thing you can do with this order is return it at your own cost for a full refund. You have modified our part and you are saying the item is in another country, correct? If you wish to proceed with the refund, please send back the order in the original box and packaging. You must have the original box and packaging.
Thank you,
